         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0771">
               <p>Married to <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0770.xml"/>Bartholomew
                     Gallatin</persName> in <date when="1746-05">May 1746</date>, Lucia (née
                  Foulkes) corresponded with all the chief leaders of British Methodism, both
                  Arminian and Calvinist. Something of her own character and her travels as the wife
                  of a field officer in the dragoons may be traced by means of the thirty-three
                  letters written to her by <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0879.xml"/>William
                     Grimshaw</persName>; cf. Frank Baker, <hi rend="italic">William Grimshaw</hi>
                     (<placeName>London</placeName>: <placeName>Epworth</placeName>, <date
                     when="1963">1963</date>), 217–30, 275–77.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
